<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 05 at 10:13PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Scotland County
through 1115 PM EDT...
At 1013 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laurinburg, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Maxton, Wagram, Gibson, East Laurinburg and Laurel Hill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
